        <p><!-- 
There is a dharmacakra symbol in the left margin adjacent to line 1. This is noted as deco, but if we include siddham symbols/characters in the margin as textparts, then maybe this too could be added to the edition. 
--><lb n="1"/>saṁvvatsara-śate paṁca<surplus>s</surplus>-tri<supplied reason="lost">ṁ</supplied>śottaratame <num value="135"><g type="numeral">100</g><g type="numeral">30</g> 5</num> puṣya-māse divase vi<supplied reason="lost">ṁ</supplied>ś<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->e</supplied> di <num value="20">
            <g type="numeral">20</g>
          </num> <supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> deya-dharm<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->o</supplied> yaṁ vihāra-svāminy<supplied reason="lost">ā</supplied> <lb n="2"/>devtāyā<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> yad atra puṇyaṁ tad bhavatu mātā-pitroḥ sarvva-sa<sic>tv</sic>ānāñ ca Anuttara-jñānāptaye||<!-- 
Fleet emends devtāyā to devatāyāḥ. I am not sure; I don't think this would have been a likely spelling mistake back then. The ligature vt is quite clear, though it could be something else as far as Fleet's rubbing shows, e.g. vg, perhaps even a misshapen ṅg or cch with the bottom left part missing. 
--><!-- 
The punctuation at the end of l2 is a double daṇḍa; the first one is hooked on the top left. 
--></p>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="1">
          <l n="a"><lb n="3"/>saubhāgyaṁ pratir<choice>
              <sic>u</sic>
              <corr>ū</corr>
            </choice>patā guṇavatī kīrttis sapatna-kṣayaḥ</l>
          <l n="b">śrīman<unclear>t</unclear>o vibhavā bhavā<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> sukha-phalā nirvvāṇam aṁte śivaM</l>
          <!-- 
The halanta M seems to be a full-sized subscript character, but the rubbing is not clear. 
-->
          <l n="c"><lb n="4"/>A-sta<unclear>bdhā</unclear>ni bhavanti dāna-niratau cittaṁ niyojyaikadā</l>
          <l n="d"><seg subtype="consonant" type="component">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="illegible" unit="component"/>
            </seg>ī <seg met="++-">
              <gap quantity="3" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
            </seg> vi<choice>
              <unclear>c</unclear>
              <unclear>t</unclear>
            </choice>āraṇa <seg met="--">
              <gap quantity="2" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
            </seg> dhiyāṁ <seg met="++-++">
              <gap quantity="5" reason="illegible" unit="character"/>
            </seg> <seg subtype="consonant" type="component">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="illegible" unit="component"/>
            </seg>iyāM<!-- 
The final halanta M is altogether indistinct in the rubbing. 
--></l>
        </lg>
